AGENT BlueAgent
VERSION 0.1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 3
PURPOSE Defensive analysis agent for constitutional adversarial sandbox
GOAL Receive attack results from RedAgent, attempt detection using AXIOM
     defenses, propose constitutional fixes for detected attacks, and
     document gaps as new bug patterns for missed attacks

RECEIVES attack_result: AttackResult, attack_report: AttackReport, hmac_key: bytes
EMITS blue_result: BlueResult, blue_report: BlueReport
MUTATES nothing — all fixes are proposals requiring human review
CANNOT_MUTATE trust_level, isolation, human_review_required, cannot_auto_promote_fixes

CONSTRAINT TRUST_LEVEL is 3 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT ISOLATION is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT human_review_required is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT cannot_auto_promote_fixes is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT Confidence values are clamped to range 0.15 through 0.85
CONSTRAINT Fix proposals are never auto-applied — always require human review
CONSTRAINT All payloads are UTF-8 encoded before HMAC signing per BUG-003 and BUG-008
CONSTRAINT HMAC signing always calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007
CONSTRAINT BlueResult signature is computed via HMAC-SHA256 over canonical fields

RULES
- Define TRUST_LEVEL as 3 integer CANNOT_MUTATE enforced via module setattr guard
- Define ISOLATION as True boolean CANNOT_MUTATE enforced via module setattr guard
- Define HUMAN_REVIEW_REQUIRED as True boolean CANNOT_MUTATE
- Define CANNOT_AUTO_PROMOTE_FIXES as True boolean CANNOT_MUTATE
- On detect_guard_pattern_match: check compiled regex patterns against attack payload
- On detect_manifold_distance: compute constitutional_distance and check threshold
- On detect_hmac_violation: check for forged or invalid HMAC signatures in payload
- On detect_cannot_mutate: detect CANNOT_MUTATE field modification attempts in payload
- On detect_semantic_similarity: compute cosine distance from known attack embeddings
- On run_defense: execute all 5 detection methods, select highest confidence match, emit BlueResult
- On run_all_defenses: iterate AttackReport results, collect BlueResults, emit signed BlueReport
- On missed attack: document gap as new bug pattern with cluster_id for weak region
- On detected attack: propose constitutional fix with confidence and detection method
- All confidence values are clamped via min(0.85, max(0.15, raw_confidence))
- All serialization uses ensure_ascii=True and explicit utf-8 encoding per BUG-003 and BUG-008

PROCESS
- BlueAgent is instantiated with hmac_key
- Caller passes AttackResult from RedAgent to run_defense
- Each detection method evaluates the attack payload independently
- Highest confidence detection is selected as the primary detection
- If any method detects the attack, BlueResult.detected is True with fix proposal
- If no method detects the attack, BlueResult.detected is False with gap documentation
- BlueResult is HMAC-signed over canonical fields
- run_all_defenses iterates all results and aggregates into BlueReport
- BlueReport computes HMAC-SHA256 signature over serialized BlueResults

CHECK
- run_defense on PROMPT_INJECTION emits BlueResult with detected True
- run_defense on TRUST_ESCALATION emits BlueResult with detected True
- run_defense on ENCODING_CONFUSION emits BlueResult with detected True
- run_all_defenses emits BlueReport with result count matching input
- BlueResult HMAC signature verifies against independently computed digest
- BlueReport HMAC signature verifies against independently computed digest
- Confidence below 0.15 is clamped to 0.15
- Confidence above 0.85 is clamped to 0.85
- human_review_required assignment raises AttributeError
- cannot_auto_promote_fixes assignment raises AttributeError
- TRUST_LEVEL assignment raises AttributeError
- ISOLATION assignment raises AttributeError

WHEN
- attack_received:    activate DefenseAnalysis
- report_received:    activate AggregateDefense
- attack_missed:      activate GapDocumentation

FAILURE
- On detection method error: log warning, continue to next method
- On all methods failing: emit BlueResult with detected False and gap documentation
- On HMAC signing failure: propagate error to caller

CONCEPT DefensiveAnalysis
PURPOSE Detect adversarial attacks using layered constitutional defenses
APPLIES WHEN BlueAgent receives AttackResult from RedAgent
NOT WHEN running without sandbox isolation
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES compiled guard patterns, constitutional distance metrics, known attack embeddings
EFFECT Detected attacks receive fix proposals; missed attacks become documented gaps

CONCEPT ConstitutionalFixProposal
PURPOSE Generate actionable fix proposals for detected attacks
APPLIES WHEN detection confidence exceeds minimum threshold
NOT WHEN fix would be auto-promoted without human review
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES human_review_required is True
EFFECT Fix proposals are queued for human review, never auto-applied

OUTPUT
- blue_result: BlueResult with attack_vector, detected, detection_method, fix_proposal, confidence, cluster_id, signature
- blue_report: BlueReport with results list, HMAC signature, timestamp, detected_count, missed_count

SUCCESS
all_detections_attempted:    0.20
hmac_signature_valid:        0.20
confidence_clamped:          0.20
cannot_mutate_enforced:      0.20
human_review_enforced:       0.20
